Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveAfrobeat singer, Femi Anikulapo Kuti, has reacted to a joke about him being nominated again for the Grammys next year.
Kuti had been nominated in the Best Global Music Album category, which was won by veteran singer, Angelique Kidjo, on Sunday.
Reacting to the win, a tweep, Man of Letters, tweeted, “Femi Kuti when Grammy nominates him again next year.”
He added a clip of a Nollywood actor saying, “What’s your problem? Why are you stressing my life for Christ’s sake.”
Kuti reacted to the tweet with laughter, saying, “I laughed die meanwhile congratulations to #angeliquekidjo ”
Femi and his son Made were nominated for their Legacy+ album.
